						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kulōttuṅga-chōladēva III: Year 22 = 1199-1200 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription records that a certain person (name not clear but probably reads as Iṉaṉ) of the same Tirukkachchūr had obtained 32 cows and a bull from the <hi rend="italic">bhaṇḍāra</hi> of the temple of the god Tiruvālakkōyiluḍaiyār and <hi rend="italic">in lieu</hi> thereof had agreed to burn a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp in the temple by measuring one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee perpetually.</p>						

						</summary>
